	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Using Blender</h1>
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Minetest Wiki</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>3D models can be used to change the appearance of <a href="/Player" title="Player">players</a>, <a href="/Node" class="mw-redirect" title="Node">nodes</a>, <a href="/Mobs" title="Mobs">mobs</a> and other <a href="/index.php?title=Entity&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Entity (page does not exist)">entities</a>.
</p><p>If you need to create models for your <a href="/Mod" class="mw-redirect" title="Mod">mod</a>, it is recommended that you use <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.blender.org/">Blender</a>.
</p>
